description:
File: python/src/lichen/client/lci.py, lines 755-758

The _str_or_none helper converts any non-None value to string:

```python
def _str_or_none(value: Any) -> str | None:
    if value is None:
        return None
    return str(value)
```

Problem: If value is bytes, str(bytes_value) produces a repr like "b'hello'" instead of decoding it:

```python
>>> str(b'hello')
"b'hello'"  # NOT 'hello'
```

This affects fields like 'body' in MessageRecord where CBOR might return bytes for text content.

Impact: Message bodies or other string fields could display as "b'...'" in the UI instead of the actual decoded text.

Fix: Add explicit bytes handling:
```python
def _str_or_none(value: Any) -> str | None:
    if value is None:
        return None
    if isinstance(value, bytes):
        return value.decode('utf-8', errors='replace')
    return str(value)
```
